about.summary: The Bootstrap framework lets you add some JavaScript functionality to your web site by adding attributes to your HTML tags - Bootstrap takes care of the JavaScript <https://getbootstrap.com/javascript>. If you are using R Markdown or Shiny, you can use these functions to create collapsible sections, accordion panels, modals, tooltips, popovers, and an accordion sidebar framework (not described at Bootstrap site).

name: r-bsplus
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.1.2' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-bsplus
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/bsplus_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/bsplus/bsplus_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: c15e26ce30ebe70fb4bfd71a7be85aa1ecb8d1679782d17d1d6e1e4b93437fa7

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-glue
    - r-htmltools
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-lubridate
    - r-magrittr
    - r-purrr
    - r-rmarkdown
    - r-stringr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-glue
    - r-htmltools
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-lubridate
    - r-magrittr
    - r-purrr
    - r-rmarkdown
    - r-stringr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('bsplus')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('bsplus')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/ijlyttle/bsplus
  license: MIT
  summary: The Bootstrap framework lets you add some JavaScript functionality to your web site
    by adding attributes to your HTML tags - Bootstrap takes care of the JavaScript
    <https://getbootstrap.com/javascript>. If you are using R Markdown or Shiny, you
    can use these functions to create collapsible sections, accordion panels, modals,
    tooltips, popovers, and an accordion sidebar framework (not described at Bootstrap
    site).
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
